  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2007-05-10",
    "date": "2009-08-19T18:02:28Z",
    "text": "Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow affiliated life and non-life insurance companies to file consolidated tax returns.\n\nAllows: (1) a phasein, between 2007 and 2013, of the full application of losses of affiliated non-life insurance companies against the taxable income of an affiliated life insurance company; and (2) an automatic waiver of the five-year waiting period applicable to affiliated non-life insurance companies for offset of their losses against life insurance company income."
